OL,3,CWatchdog concludes probe into fatal
OL,4,Caccident at Stratford Underground
OL,5,CStation
OL,7,FThe RIAB's first recommendation to
OL,8,FLondon Underground Limited urges the
OL,9,Fimplementation of technology to detect
OL,10,Fpassengers in dangerous positions and
OL,11,Fautomatically warn or stop trains as
OL,12,Fneeded. The second calls for a review
OL,13,Fof environmental, organisational, and
OL,14,Fjob factors associated with automatic
OL,15,Ftrain operation to address how
OL,16,F"underload" affects operator
OL,17,Fperformance. Additionally, staff were
OL,18,Freminded of the critical importance of
OL,19,Fusing proper safety communications
OL,20,Fwhen reporting and managing incidents.
